post_text:
Tomorrow is the first day of school!!! We are excited to have students back in the building. As we start school, we ask everyone to be flexible as we navigate this “New Normal” era! We are also making sure that we do everything to keep the staff and students safe while they are at school and on the bus. Please have your child wear his or her mask to school on the bus and when they enter the building. Students will not have to wear a mask in most classes as long as they can social distance. The school is providing two masks for every student and will have hand sanitizer in every room. See everyone tomorrow!!!
Matt Rayl
6-12 Principal

post_text:
GRADUATION DETAILS:

Graduation has been finalized and scheduled for Saturday, June 27th at 2:00 pm. In order to keep the graduation ceremony as traditional as possible, under these circumstances, each Senior will be able to invite 10 guests. For those that wish to view graduation, we will be live streaming the ceremony via Facebook Live. Further information has been communicated to the Seniors and their parents. If any circumstances, requirements, etc. change prior to graduation, we will communicate via Textcaster and Facebook.

We would like to invite friends, family, and community members to our outdoor "reception" that will take place following the graduation ceremony!

*See flyers below for more information.

Amazon today canceled the subscription of books and audio stories for children and students of all ages as long as schools are closed, kids everywhere can instantly stream an incredible collection of stories, including titles across six different languages, that will help them continue dreaming, learning, and just being kids.

All stories are free to stream on your desktop, laptop, phone or tablet using the following link https://stories.audible.com/start-listen

Spread the good news.

post_text: Another fun, educational game.
shared_text:
Andrea Herrold-Pullan
March 18 at 10:23 AM ·

Another math game for you!

Ten Before Nine
Topic: Structuring
Materials: Cards 1-10
Directions:
Play begins with a student putting down one card at a time in rows of three.
As each card from the deck is shown, if it can be put with another card already down to MAKE 10, then it is placed directly on top of that number. (10 can be placed on 10)
If a card cannot be placed on any of the previous cards to MAKE 10, it is put down in its own space.
Play continues with it considered a WIN if all cards can be placed before filling 3 rows of 3 -so getting TENS before filling NINE places

Variations:
May be played with partners. One player turns over the cards while the other player-coaches them on where to put them.
Rather than 3 rows of 3, it could be one row of 9

Please see letter from Mr. Fox in response to the COVID-19 outbreak. We WILL be in session tomorrow, Wed. 3/18. It will be a modified early dismissal day. School will be dismissed at 12:10.

Our teachers have worked diligently today to prepare for the coming weeks! Please be sure your student is attendance tomorrow (if they are not sick), as we need to discuss our current educational plan moving forward.

If you see a Grundy R-V staff member, please thank them! They have been stressing and working hard to prepare for an extended amount of time away from their students. They want the best for all students and they are working hard to make this uncertainty a little more of a smooth process.

This is uncharted territory for everyone and we assure you that we are making the best decision possible for the safety and security of our students, staff, and community.

If you have any questions, please feel free to contact Administration.

#PantherPRIDE
